hooks/keystone_hooks.py.message:
I think this "regexp" only works on reactive charms. Per [1], this can be defined in 3 ways:
1) one way
```
@hooks.hook("haproxy-exporter-relation-joined")
def prometheus_relation_joined(relid=None):
    # blablabla

@hooks.hook("haproxy-exporter-relation-changed")
def prometheus_relation_changed(relid=None):
    prometheus_relation_joined(relid=relid)
```

2) second way (using the decorated.__name__, in an implicit way)
```
@hooks.hook()
haproxy_exporter_relation_joined(relid=None):
    # blablabla

@hooks.hook()
haproxy_exporter_relation_changed(relid=None):
    haproxy_exporter_relation_joined(relid=relid)
```

3) probably the best
```
@hooks.hook("haproxy-exporter-relation-joined", "haproxy-exporter-relation-changed")
def haproxy_exporter_relation_changed(relid=None):
    # blablabla
```

1. https://github.com/juju/charm-helpers/blob/master/charmhelpers/core/hookenv.py#L972

